<exploration xml:id="warm-observa-elTazonYElTarro" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>[@@@@@@@@@]</title>

<statement>
  <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Students may notice:</p>
<ul>
      <li>There is a bowl and a jar on a table.</li>
      <li>The bowl is short and wide.</li>
      <li>The jar is tall and skinny.</li>
      <li>Both containers have some water in them.</li>
    </ul>
<p>Students may wonder:</p>
<ul>
      <li>How much does each container hold?</li>
      <li>Why are the containers partially filled with water?</li>
      <li>Which container holds more?</li>
      <li>How could we measure the amount that each container would hold?</li>
    </ul>
  </solution>


