  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>10 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->  
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this warm-up is to elicit the idea that liquid volume is a measurable attribute, which will be useful when students use informal units and liters to measure liquid volume in later activities. While students may notice and wonder many things about these containers, ideas around how much each container holds and which container holds more are the important discussion points.</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Materiales requeridos de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="materials-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[mmmmmmmmmm]</p>
    <!-- <xi:include href="./warm-observa-elTazonYElTarro-mat.ptx"/>  -->
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Launch -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="launch-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Groups of 2</li>
      <li>Display the image.</li>
      <li>
        <q>¿Qué observan? ¿Qué se preguntan?</q>
      </li>
      <li>1 minute: quiet think time</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Instrucciones para el desarrollo de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="instructions-teacher-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <q>Discutan con su pareja lo que pensaron</q>
      </li>
      <li>1 minute: partner discussion</li>
      <li>Share and record responses.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</prelude>


